# Allowlist-style .gitignore: everything is ignored by default, and only
# specific files/directories are explicitly un-ignored below. This folder
# has a lot of large reference material and personal data that must never
# be committed (especially since this repo is public) -- safer to opt files
# IN one at a time than to try to opt everything else OUT.

# Deny everything at the root by default.
/*

# Allow looking inside these directories (see per-directory rules below).
!/code/
!/Photos/
!/report/
!/.gitignore
# Root pyenv selector (= "bounds") so the report env activates at the project
# root, which is where all scripts are now meant to be run from (Jul 12 2026).
!/.python-version

# Build pipeline (task-runner style; see the Makefile header for why it's not
# incremental). No secrets -- just script invocations. Added Jul 13 2026.
!/Makefile

# Reviewed by Jim and confirmed clean of personal/sensitive info (Jul 2 2026).
!/Acton Bounds TODO.md

# Jim removed Email/Phone columns from Contacts and re-exported (Jul 2 2026);
# verified clean of emails/phone numbers/Drive-Sheet IDs before allowlisting.
!/Acton Bounds.xlsx

# Reviewed and approved by Jim (Jul 3 2026) -- Project Notes.md's town clerk
# contact table is public government office info, not personal.
!/CHANGELOG.md
!/Project Notes.md

# Jim committed this directly via GitHub's web UI (Jul 3 2026); added here
# so it's reflected in the allowlist too.
!/README.md

# --- code/ ---
/code/*
!/code/*.py
!/code/claude.md
!/code/.python-version
!/code/requirements.txt
# Assembly manifest (build config, like a Makefile): scanned clean of
# IDs/PII Jul 12 2026 -- only relative paths + section names.
!/code/report_sections.csv
# Photo curation sheet (tracked Jul 15 2026). Mostly machine-derived from the
# photo filenames, but caption / include / exclude_reason / section /
# cover_candidate are Jim's hand-authored editorial decisions and are
# regenerable from nothing -- they had no durable home while this was ignored
# (Drive is explicitly not an archive). Scanned clean Jul 15 2026: no emails,
# local paths, or secrets; captions and exclude_reason are about the photos
# themselves. exclude_reason is published deliberately -- Jim's call, so a
# future Acton group can see why a photo was left out and revisit it.
# Re-scan before committing new captions, same gate as report/*.md.
!/code/photo_manifest.csv

# --- report/ ---
# Canonical report-section sources (Markdown), maintained by Claude Code and
# rendered to PDF by intro2pdf.py. Only the .md sources are tracked; the
# generated *.pdf render outputs stay ignored (build artifacts). Each .md is
# scanned for secrets/PII before it lands here (see code/claude.md).
/report/*
!/report/*.md

# --- Photos/ ---
/Photos/*
!/Photos/process_takeout.py
!/Photos/CLAUDE.md
!/Photos/requirements.txt
!/Photos/.python-version
# "Acton Bounds - SiteNames.csv" was here; deleted Jul 15 2026. A one-off Google
# Sheets export of the SiteNames sheet, read by nothing, untouched since the
# initial commit, and silently stale (it still carried a "Bay  Drive" double
# space long since fixed in the xlsx). The same names live in Acton Bounds.xlsx.
